I"<p>Puppet comes with a set of core data types like Integer, Float, String, Boolean.</p>

<p>But what if you have special needs? How to reimplement the stdlib functions like validate_absolute_path() or validate_ipv4()?</p>

<p>Puppet allows you to place your own build data types into a modules type directory:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>modulepath/
\-  firewall/
     |- manifests/
     | \- init.pp
     |- lib/
     |  |- facter
     |  \- puppet
     |- facts.d
     \- types
        \- ipv4address.pp
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Inside the types directory you can specify a new data type. This new data type is available in your module namespace:</p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code># firewall/types/ipv4address.pp
type firewall::ipv4address = Pattern[/^((([0-9](?!\d)|[1-9][0-9](?!\d)|1[0-9]{2}(?!\d)|2[0-4][0-9](?!\d)|25[0-5](?!\d))[.]){3}([0-9](?!\d)|[1-9][0-9](?!\d)|1[0-9]{2}(?!\d)|2[0-4][0-9](?!\d)|25[0-5](?!\d)))(\/((([0-9](?!\d)|[1-9][0-9](?!\d)|1[0-9]{2}(?!\d)|2[0-4][0-9](?!\d)|25[0-5](?!\d))[.]){3}([0-9](?!\d)|[1-9][0-9](?!\d)|1[0-9]{2}(?!\d)|2[0-4][0-9](?!\d)|25[0-5](?!\d))|[0-9]+))?$/]
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>You can use any data type for building new ones.</p>

<p>Some combined data types are already available in <a href="https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppetlabs-stdlib/tree/master/types">puppetlabs-stdlib</a> or <a href="https://github.com/voxpupuli/puppet-tea">voxpupuli-tea</a>.</p>

<p>Martin Alfke</p>
